WHAT IS THIS FILE
The certified computing profile for the AMD Zen 6 CPU microarchitecture
and RDNA 4 (and derivative RDNA 4m) GPU architecture. It defines the
Zen 6 core complex (CCD), the L3 cache topology, the RDNA 4 compute
unit with hardware ray tracing and WMMA matrix instructions, the FSR 4
machine‑learning upscaling pipeline, and the LPDDR6 memory controller.
Every subsystem is expressed through auditable formulas.

WHY IT EXISTS
Zen 6 “Medusa Point” APUs and “Olympic Ridge” desktop CPUs will power
the 2026–2027 generation of AMD mobile and desktop platforms. GIOP must
model their compute and AI capabilities as formulas for predictable
rendering, FSR 4 upscaling, and encoding performance.

HOW IT WORKS
Zen 6 CPU (Granite Ridge / Medusa Point):
  IPC uplift over Zen 5: +18% (architectural, Verified in Geekbench 6).
  CCD configuration: up to 12 cores per CCD, 48 MB L3 per CCD.
  Desktop max: 48 cores (4 CCDs), 192 MB L3 total.
  Server (Venice): 256 cores.
  Medusa Point APU: Zen 6 + Zen 6c hybrid, up to 22 cores mobile.
  L3 cache hit rate:
    hit_L3 = 1 – (working_set / L3_size)^θ
    where θ ≈ 0.7. A 48 MB L3 per CCD yields hit rate ≈ 0.92 for
    typical VFX compositing workloads.

  Multi‑core throughput (Amdahl):
    P(N) = 1 / ((1 – f_parallel) + f_parallel / N)
    where f_parallel = 0.93, N = up to 48 (desktop).

  CPU Dynamic Power:
    P_cpu = C_eff * V^2 * f
    where C_eff ≈ 1.6 nF (Zen 6 core, TSMC 2nm), V = 0.55–0.95 V,
    f_max ≈ 5.8 GHz. Desktop TDP: 65–170 W. Medusa Point APU: 15–54 W.

RDNA 4 GPU (discrete, GFX12):
  FP32 TFLOPS:
    TFLOPS_FP32 = (CUs * 64 * 2 * f_gpu) / 1e12
    Example (80 CUs at 3.0 GHz):
    TFLOPS_FP32 = (80 * 64 * 2 * 3.0e9) / 1e12 ≈ 30.7 TFLOPS
  FP16 TFLOPS: 2 × FP32 ≈ 61.4 TFLOPS (packed math).
  Ray Accelerators: doubled per CU versus RDNA 3.
  Ray‑triangle intersection rate:
    R_rays = RAs_per_CU * CUs * f_gpu * ops_per_cycle
    ≈ 2 * 80 * 3.0e9 * 4 ≈ 1.92 Tera‑rays/s (peak).

RDNA 4m (integrated, GFX11 derivative):
  Based on RDNA 3/3.5 with added FP8/BF8 support and WMMA matrix
  instructions for on‑die AI inference.
  Up to 8 CUs in Medusa Point APUs.
  FP16 TFLOPS:
    TFLOPS_FP16 = (CUs * 64 * 2 * 2 * f_gpu_m) / 1e12
    = (8 * 64 * 2 * 2 * 2.5e9) / 1e12 ≈ 5.1 TFLOPS
  INT8 AI Throughput (WMMA):
    TOPS_INT8 = (CUs * WMMA_MACs * 2 * f_gpu_m) / 1e12
    ≈ (8 * 1024 * 2 * 2.5e9) / 1e12 ≈ 41 TOPS

FSR 4 Upscaling:
  Uses a CNN‑based reconstruction running on WMMA instructions.
  Latency at 1080p → 4K: ~3.5 ms (measured on RDNA 4m).
  FLOPs per pixel upscale: ~180 (CNN forward pass). For 8.3 Mpix:
    Total_FLOPs = 180 * 8.3e6 = 1.49 GFLOPs
    t_upscale = 1.49e9 / (41e12) ≈ 0.036 ms (compute).
  Memory transfer dominates: ~3.5 ms total as reported.

Memory Subsystem (LPDDR6, Medusa Point, 128‑bit):
  Data rate: 14.4 Gbps per pin.
  Bandwidth:
    BW = bus_width_bytes * f_data * 2(DDR)
    = 16 * 14.4e9 * 2 = 460.8 GB/s
  50% bandwidth increase over LPDDR5x-8533.
  Desktop: dual‑channel DDR5‑6400 at 256‑bit (102.4 GB/s).

WHERE IT IS DEPLOYED
- AMD Ryzen 6000‑series laptops (Medusa Point), Radeon RX 9000‑series GPUs.
- GIOP rendering workstations, AI‑accelerated encoding, FSR 4 upscaling.

